  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Creative Technologist",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We’re looking for a <strong>Creative Technologist to support the creation of interactive and technology-driven experiences.</strong> You’ll collaborate with internal teams across creative, strategy, production, and client services to help deliver digital and experiential solutions for events, campaigns, and brand activations.</p><p><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist in the <strong>conceptualisation and development</strong> of interactive, digital, and experiential projects</li><li>Support the creation of <strong>prototypes, demos, and technical tests</strong> for pitches and live events</li><li>Help translate creative ideas into <strong>technical executions</strong>, with guidance from senior team members</li><li>Collaborate with designers, developers, and production partners during project builds and event setups, demonstrating <strong>strong teamwork and initiative</strong></li><li>Support <strong>testing, troubleshooting, and on-site technical execution</strong> during rehearsals and live events</li><li>Research and explore <strong>new technologies, tools, and interactive methods</strong> to enhance experiential projects</li><li>Document processes, learn best practices, and contribute to continuous improvement in project delivery</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or degree in <strong>creative technology, interactive media, digital design, engineering, or related fields</strong></li><li>Basic understanding of <strong>interactive or digital technologies</strong></li><li>Familiarity with one or more of the following is a plus (not mandatory):</li><li><li>Creative coding tools (TouchDesigner, Unity, Unreal, Processing, p5.js)</li><li>Web technologies (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)</li><li>Physical computing (Arduino, Raspberry Pi, sensors)</li></li><li>Hands-on experience from <strong>projects, internships, or personal work</strong> is welcome</li><li><strong>Strong team player</strong> who is motivated to get hands-on and contribute across multiple aspects of a project</li><li>Willingness to learn, experiment, and take initiative</li><li>Comfortable working in a <strong>fast-paced, project-based environment</strong></li></ul><p><br /><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><p>Curious, open-minded, and eager to explore new ideas and technologies</p><p>A <strong>collaborative team player</strong> who enjoys working closely with different disciplines</p><p>Detail-oriented and able to <strong>adapt quickly</strong> during live events and builds</p><p>Passionate about creating <strong>memorable, technology-driven experiences</strong></p>",
